mitelCs2000SysName.name: mitelCs2000SysName
mitelCs2000SysName.description: The name of the call server.

mitelCs2000AlmLevel.name: mitelCs2000AlmLevel
mitelCs2000AlmLevel.description: The current overall alarm level for the call server.

mitelCs2000AlmDetectDate.name: mitelCs2000AlmDetectDate
mitelCs2000AlmDetectDate.description: Defines when the alarm was detected.

mitelCs2000AlmNbrCategories.name: mitelCs2000AlmNbrCategories
mitelCs2000AlmNbrCategories.description: Defines the number of associated entries in the categories table.

mitelCs2000CategoryTable.name: mitelCs2000CategoryTable
mitelCs2000CategoryTable.description: Table defining the alarm state for individual call server categories. There will be multiple categories for each call server. The number of rows in the table is determined by the total of the mitelCs2000AlmTblNbrCategories value.

mitelCs2000CategoryTableEntry.name: mitelCs2000CategoryTableEntry
mitelCs2000CategoryTableEntry.description: A row defining a single category.

mitelCs2000CatTblIndex.name: mitelCs2000CatTblIndex
mitelCs2000CatTblIndex.description: Differentiates the different category reports for the call server. The first category will have an index value of 1, the second will have 2, etc. up to the last category report. The highest possible index value is 100.

mitelCs2000CatTblAvailable.name: mitelCs2000CatTblAvailable
mitelCs2000CatTblAvailable.description: The number of available resources of this type of category on this call server.

mitelCs2000CatTblUnavailable.name: mitelCs2000CatTblUnavailable
mitelCs2000CatTblUnavailable.description: The number of unavailable resources of this type of category on this call server.

mitelCs2000CatTblLevel.name: mitelCs2000CatTblLevel
mitelCs2000CatTblLevel.description: Defines the alarm level for this category on this call server.

mitelCs2000CatTblMinorThresh.name: mitelCs2000CatTblMinorThresh
mitelCs2000CatTblMinorThresh.description: The percentage unavailable threshold indicating a minor alarm on this call server category.

mitelCs2000CatTblMajorThresh.name: mitelCs2000CatTblMajorThresh
mitelCs2000CatTblMajorThresh.description: The percentage unavailable threshold indicating a major alarm on this call server category.

mitelCs2000CatTblCriticalThresh.name: mitelCs2000CatTblCriticalThresh
mitelCs2000CatTblCriticalThresh.description: The percentage unavailable threshold indicating a critical alarm on this call server category.

mitelCs2000CatTblName.name: mitelCs2000CatTblName
mitelCs2000CatTblName.description: The name of this resource category.

mitelCs2000NotifAlarm.name: mitelCs2000NotifAlarm
mitelCs2000NotifAlarm.description: This notification is generated whenever an alarm condition is detected or cleared. The manager is expected to retrieve the corresponding alarm and category table information.
